## API Conventions

### Endpoints

- Use RESTful naming: `/resources/{id}`
- Version in URL: `/api/v1/...`
- Use plural nouns: `/users` not `/user`

### HTTP Methods

| Method | Usage |
|--------|-------|
| GET | Retrieve resources |
| POST | Create new resource |
| PUT | Replace resource |
| PATCH | Partial update |
| DELETE | Remove resource |

### Status Codes

| Code | Usage |
|------|-------|
| 200 | Success |
| 201 | Created |
| 400 | Bad Request |
| 401 | Unauthorized |
| 403 | Forbidden |
| 404 | Not Found |
| 500 | Server Error |

## Validation

- MUST validate all request inputs
- MUST sanitize user-provided data
{{#if fastapi}}
- Use Pydantic models for request/response validation
{{/if}}
{{#if express}}
- Use Zod or Joi for validation
{{/if}}

## Error Handling

Return structured error responses:

```json
{
  "error": {
    "code": "VALIDATION_ERROR",
    "message": "Human readable message",
    "details": {}
  }
}
```

## Security

- NEVER log sensitive data (passwords, tokens)
- MUST use parameterized queries (no SQL injection)
- MUST validate file uploads (size, type)
- MUST implement rate limiting on public endpoints
